      "rationale": "NIH is the FDA-accepted metric for haemolysis quantification per ASTM F1841. Physiological linkage documented: NIH > 0.1 g/100 L associated with clinically significant haemolysis in published literature (Paul et al. 2003). Sensitivity analysis confirms wall shear stress exposure time (τ·t) accounts for 61% of NIH variance; pressure head gradient contributes 18%. QoI hierarchy fully justified."
